item.title: /317/*project* -[null]- /317/
item.dc:creator: @k_to_the_oed k to the oed
item.description:
@k_to_the_oed wrote:

When you actually get onto the server and see how much is wrong with it, even though it is very nice… its not worth it.
1st problem - Cant see where teleports tele you to… and half of them don’t work.
2nd - Skill cape masters are just for show, they dont really do anything…whats the point?
3rd - Theres 5 error’s in the source file which are almost unfixable…
4th - Clan chat doesn’t work.
5th - Skill cape emote doesn’t work.
6th - Horrible combat between NPCS. (decent with players)

PROBLEMS I FIXED -
1 - skill cape masters now sell skill capes and items you need to train there skill with.
2 -(some/most) Skill cape emote’s work its got the gfx and anim’s of a 508 cache.
3 - All 5 errors fixed…took me 3 days lol…
4 - Clan Chat works decently (holds a maximum of 20 players)
5 - Made combat emotes, and timer work on npcs/When PvPing there timer is still a little slow when you try to attack somone, but the animations and gfx’s work 100%.
6 - Home teleport works now
7 - there is now a dialogue box in the spells book so you can see where your teleporting now…
8 - added 508 deob interfaces.
9 - Made worn items interface equipt the items your wearing… i just took the makeover mage interface pretty much and added it to the worn items interface…

I’m gonna finish up the server by adding a new home, new shopping erea, theiving teleport, pk box and some other stuff and im gonna post it up on mopar’s server downloads if you guys wana see… it’ll be alot diffrent from the source right now so if you wana call it leeching… take a look at it first…

Credits for when i get done with it :
40% Me.
10% Empirescape for client.
40% ModAssasian/Mod Null for source
10% Delta for original base.
